1 Animal agriculture facility infrastructure fund - State treasurer - Continuing
2 appropriation.
3 1. The animal agriculture facility infrastructure fund is created as a special fund in the
4 state treasury. The fund consists of all moneys transferred to the fund under
5 subsection 2. All moneys in the fund are appropriated to the the state treasurer on a
6 continuing basis for the purpose of providing distributions to counties.
7 2. Notwithstanding any other provision of law, after the allocations under sections
8 57 - 39.2 - 26.1, 57 - 39.2 - 26.2, 57 - 39.2 - 26.3, and 57 - 39.2 - 26.4, a portion of sales, gross
9 receipts, and use tax collections equal to the combined total of the amounts under
10 subsection 3 must be deposited by the state treasurer in the animal agriculture facility
11 infrastructure fund as needed. The tax commissioner shall calculate the amount
12 needed for distributions under subsection 3 and shall certify to the state treasurer the
13 portion of sales, gross receipts, and use tax net revenues that must be deposited in
14 the fund to provide for the distributions.
15 3. At least once per fiscal year, the state treasurer shall distribute to each county the
16 amount certified by the tax commissioner. The amount certified by the tax
17 commissioner each fiscal year for each county is the sum of the state portion of sales,
18 gross receipts, and use tax imposed under this title on eligible tangible personal
19 property purchased to construct or repair animal agriculture facilities located in the
20 county or to operate or repair equipment used in animal agriculture facilities located in
21 the county based on documentation of proof of purchase submitted to the tax
22 commissioner during the fiscal year. Documentation of proof of purchase must be
23 submitted in the form and manner prescribed by the tax commissioner.
24 4. A county shall use the funding distributed under this section for infrastructure projects
25 near animal agriculture facilities located in the county or for other county expenses.
